```json
{
  "application": "Slurm",
  "details": {
    "job_name": "selfsupervised",
    "mail_type": "END",
    "mail_user": "benweinstein2010@gmail.com",
    "account": "ewhite",
    "nodes": 1,
    "cpus_per_task": 1,
    "mem": "50GB",
    "time": "48:00:00",
    "output": "/home/b.weinstein/logs/DeepTreeAttention_%j.out",
    "error": "/home/b.weinstein/logs/DeepTreeAttention_%j.err",
    "conda_environment": "DeepTreeAttention",
    "python_script": "notebooks/crop_random_tile.py"
  }
}
```

This script uses Slurm as the workload manager. The script sets various parameters for the job, including:

- **Job Name:** selfsupervised
- **Mail Events:** END (email is sent only when the job finishes)
- **Mail User:** benweinstein2010@gmail.com
- **Account:** ewhite
- **Nodes:** 1 (single node)
- **CPUs per Task:** 1 (single core per task)
- **Memory:** 50 GB
- **Time Limit:** 48 hours
- **Output Log:** /home/b.weinstein/logs/DeepTreeAttention_%j.out
- **Error Log:** /home/b.weinstein/logs/DeepTreeAttention_%j.err

The script also activates a conda environment named "DeepTreeAttention" and runs a Python script called "crop_random_tile.py" within the "DeepTreeAttention" directory.
